#. Tag: date
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "2003-03-08"
msgstr "8 de marzo de 2003"

#. Tag: manvolnum
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>"
msgstr "<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "fool <command>make</command> into not rebuilding certain files"
msgstr ""
"Enganar a <command>make</command> para non recompilar certos ficheiros."

#. Tag: cmdsynopsis
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> <group><option>hidechange</option> "
"<replaceable>file</replaceable></group> <group><option>show</option></group> "
"<group><option>why</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable></group>"
msgstr ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> <group><option>hidechange</option> "
"<replaceable>ficheiro</replaceable></group> <group><option>show</option></"
"group> <group><option>why</option> <replaceable>ficheiro</replaceable></"
"group>"

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Descrición"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> is used to save time when recompiling. It can "
"fool make into skipping files that haven't changed in a meaningful way. This "
"can be used for instance when you change a comment in a file but none of the "
"actual code."
msgstr ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> é usado para aforrar tempo ao recompilar. Pode "
"enganar a make para que salte ficheiros que non fosen cambiados dun xeito "
"significativo. Pode usarse, por exemplo, se cambia un comentario nun "
"ficheiro pero non o código efectivo."

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "This utility is part of the &kde; Software Development Kit."
msgstr ""
"Esta utilidade forma parte do equipamento de desenvolvemento de programas de "
"&kde;."

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Opcións"

#. Tag: term
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>hidechange</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>hidechange</option> <replaceable>ficheiro</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hides the fact that file was changed by setting the timestamp into the past. "
"Use with care!"
msgstr ""
"Oculta que o ficheiro cambiou poñendo a marca de tempo no pasado. Úsese con "
"precaución!"

#. Tag: option
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "show"
msgstr "show"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lists what files <command>make</command> currently needs to rebuild"
msgstr ""
"Lista os ficheiros que <command>make</command> debe recompilar na actualidade"

#. Tag: term
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>why</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>why</option> <replaceable>ficheiro</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Explains why make must rebuild file"
msgstr "Explica por que debe recompilar make o ficheiro"

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Environment"
msgstr "Contorno"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One of the following variables (but not both) should be set if the source "
"directory is different from the build directory. If the build directory is "
"simply a subdirectory of the source directory, the simpler variable "
"<envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> should be used."
msgstr ""
"Unha das seguintes variábeis (pero non ambas as dúas) debe estar definida se "
"o cartafol das fontes non é o mesmo que o do código obxecto. Se o do código "
"obxecto é simplemente un subcartafol do das fontes, debe usarse a variábel "
"<envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar>, máis simple."

#. Tag: envar
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "OBJ_SUBJDIR"
msgstr "OBJ_SUBJDIR"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Indicates that the build directory is in the given subdirectory of the "
"source directory. For instance, if the source directory is <filename class="
"\"directory\">kdesdk</filename> and the build directory is <filename class="
"\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, then <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</"
"envar> should be set to <parameter>obj-i386-linux</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Indica que o cartafol do código obxecto está no subcartafol indicado do das "
"fontes. Por exemplo, se o cartafol das fontes é <filename class=\"directory"
"\">kdesdk</filename> e o do código obxecto é <filename class=\"directory"
"\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, entón <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> debe "
"definirse como <parameter>obj-i386-linux</parameter>."

#. Tag: envar
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "OBJ_REPLACEMENT"
msgstr "OBJ_REPLACEMENT"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <command>sed</command> expression that is used to transform the source "
"directory into the build directory. For instance, if the source directory is "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, then "
"<envar>OBJ_REPLACEMENT</envar> should be set to <parameter>s#kdesdk#kdesdk-"
"obj#</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Unha expresión de <command>sed</command> que se usa para transformar o "
"cartafol das fontes no de compilación. Por exemplo, se o das fontes é "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, entón "
"<envar>OBJ_REPLACEMENT</envar> debe definirse como "
"<parameter>s#kdesdk#kdesdk-obj#</parameter>."

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "See Also"
msgstr "Consulte tamén"

